column1: Nonfatal Hospitalized Injuries, Both Sexes, Ages 0 to 19 , United States, 2010
Estimated Number of Nonfatal Injuries and Average and Total Lifetime Costs
Injury Classification Scheme: Mechanism by Intent of Injury.
Reports for All Ages include those of unknown age.

* Cost estimates based on 20 or fewer injury cases, a national (weighted) estimate of 1200 or fewer cases, or with a coefficient of variation (CV) greater than 30% may be unstable.  Interpret with caution.
Produced by: National Center for Injury Prevention and Control, CDC
Data Source: NCHS Vital Statistics System for numbers of deaths. NEISS All Injury Program operated by the U.S. Consumer Product Safety
Commission (CPSC) for numbers of nonfatal injuries. Pacific Institute for Research and Evaluation (PIRE), Calverton, MD for unit cost estimates.

Subset:  (where=(left(years) between '2010' and '2010' and ( left(intent) in( '1' ) ) and ( mech2 in( 17 ,18 ) ) and ( agegrp between  0  and  3 )))  (For Regional/State Price runs, Region/State appears in a separate column.)
